entry.title: Papers to read
entry.summary:
This is a long and constantly updated list of useful resources for study. There is no particular order, and I will probably find a structure that makes for these papers, but for now they are just group by random categories that are only meaningful to myself.

CSE 250A material: * belief networks are the precursor to unsupervised learning.

Information Theory: * Claude Shannon was both a great philosopher and mathematician.
